<div class="comment" id="comment-47769960">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/embedding-shape">embedding-shape</a> 19 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">Ironically, I live in Spain, and at this very minute, there is a football game going on (Atlético Madrid vs Barcelona) which I literally just learned about because I could just hear my neighbors scream about the 0-1 score, and with Vodafone ISP I&#x27;m not experiencing the block of Cloudflare right now. <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;hayahora.futbol&#x2F;" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;hayahora.futbol&#x2F;</a> also shows &quot;NO&quot; incorrectly (if you&#x27;re being strict about the title+domain). I&#x27;m guessing it&#x27;s specifically because it isn&#x27;t a La Liga game, it&#x27;s UEFA Champions League. At least ISPs aren&#x27;t indiscriminately blocking things without court orders, which seems to have been specifically about La Liga.</div>
